      "sha256": "2727ad641632f5e10bd1df8ac741630a8dbd1b2c8cdc135c0701a014382412d2",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Let $\\hat{R}(G)$ denote the size Ramsey number, the minimal number of edges $m$ such that there is a graph $H$ with $m$ edges that is Ramsey for $G$.\n\nIs there a function $f$ such that $f(x)/x\\to \\infty$ as $x\\to \\infty$ such that, for all large $C$, if $G$ is a graph with $n$ vertices and $e\\geq Cn$ edges then\\[\\hat{R}(G) > f(C) e?\\]"
    }
  },
